1.en: But the US campaign was undermined by fears it was trying to push down the dollar by the Federal Reserve's return to quantitative easing.
1.cn: 但是，美联储重拾量化宽松措施，引发了有关美国试图以此压低美元汇率的担忧，从而削弱了上述行动的效果。

2.en: But, because of the large population, the reserve per capita is less than half of that of the world.
2.cn: 但因中国人口众多，人均资源占有量不及世界平均水平的一半。

3.en: The depreciation of the US dollar raises once again the question of how long the natural life of a reserve currency can be.
3.cn: 近期美元贬值，再次令人想起储备货币的自然寿命究竟有多长的问题。

0.en: For a slightly wilder experience explore the jungle paths of the Bukit Timah Nature Reserve.
0.cn: 想要更刺激的体验？那便要来到武吉知马自然保护区，在森林小径探险。

1.en: Hell, it took you long enough. I was getting the grand reserve. Only for our most distinguished guests.
1.cn: 怎么这么久才来？我去取特级珍藏的酒了，仅供给我们最高贵的客人。

2.en: Look, you probably can't read, fox, but the sign says we reserve the right to refuse service to anyone! So beat it.
2.cn: 你是不识字吗，狐狸，看这个，我们有权拒绝提供服务，快走吧。

3.en: Which brings us to article 23 subsection C, please check here to reserve your spot at the ten year roommate reunion.
3.cn: 请看到第23条第C款，请在这里签名来预留十年后室友团聚会的位子。

4.en: In fact, monetary policy is set by an independent Federal Reserve System, or The Fed, made up of 12 regional banks in major cities around the country.
4.cn: 事实上，货币政策是由独立的联邦准备系统制定，也就是联准会，其下有十二家区域银行散布在美国的各大都市。

5.en: In fact, monetary policy is set by an independent Federal Reserve System, or The Fed, made up of 12 regional banks in major cities around the country.
5.cn: 事实上，货币政策是由独立的联邦准备系统制定，也就是联准会，其下有十二家区域银行散布在美国的各大都市。

6.en: Harsh terms. But all right I'll just substitute "intercourse." Great. Or "fornication." Yeah. But that has judgmental overtones, so I'll hold that in reserve.
6.cn: 协议条款真苛刻，不过没关系，我可以用“性交”代替。这下好了。或者用“私通”，但这个带有批评色彩，还是作为备用吧。

7.en: As a deterrent. A silver bullet to keep in reserve, to use against the Kryptonians, so the day does not come, madam, when your children are waving daisies at a reviewing stand.
7.cn: 作为一种威慑手段，一颗随时准备好的银子弹，可以用来对付氪星人，这样那一天就不会到来，女士，你的孩子站在阅兵台上挥舞雏菊的那一天。
